<LocalizedProperties><Language>en</Language><Title>Security Update for Windows XP (KB970483)</Title><Description>A security issue has been identified that could allow an anonymous remote attacker to bypass authentication requirements of running Internet Information Services (IIS). You can help protect your system by installing this update from Microsoft. After you install this update, you may have to restart your system.</Description><UninstallNotes>This software update can be removed via Add or Remove Programs in Control Panel.</UninstallNotes><MoreInfoUrl>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=150568</MoreInfoUrl><SupportUrl>http://support.microsoft.com</SupportUrl></LocalizedProperties>